name: r-cubelyr
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.0.2" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-cubelyr
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/cubelyr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/cubelyr/cubelyr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 18b10f1fe561305a1e115a438460264b88b301b3e8c086b931500a798be39b94

build:
  number: 3
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr
    - r-glue
    - r-pillar
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyselect
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr
    - r-glue
    - r-pillar
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyselect

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('cubelyr')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('cubelyr')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/hadley/cubelyr
  license: MIT
  summary: An implementation of a data cube extracted out of 'dplyr' for backward compatibility.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
